    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "language": "python",
        "pythonCode": "from datetime import datetime\nimport random\n# Get real current date and time\nnow = datetime.now()\ndate_str = now.strftime(\"%m/%d/%Y\")\ntime_str = now.strftime(\"%H:%M\")\n# Define some dynamic hooks and actions\nhook_phrases = [\n    \"When {character} {action}!\",\n    \"You won't believe what {character} does!\",\n    \"Watch {character} {action} in pastel magic!\",\n    \"I can't believe {character} just {action}!\",\n    \"{character} {action} and it's adorable!\"\n]\nactions = [\n    \"dances in the candy clouds\",\n    \"discovers a rainbow waterfall\",\n    \"giggles while floating on lanterns\",\n    \"throws a sparkly magic spell\",\n    \"plays hide-and-seek in the pastel garden\",\n    \"slides down a fluffy cloud slide\",\n    \"spins under the twinkling stars\",\n    \"sings with magical sparkles around\",\n    \"jumps between floating petals\"\n]\n# Example character (you can replace with your generated character)\ncharacter = random.choice([\n    \"Cheerful Girl in Pink\", \n    \"Tiny Mermaid Girl\", \n    \"Adorable Elf Girl\", \n    \"Joyful Princess\", \n    \"Cute Wizard Girl\", \n    \"Playful School Girl\"\n])\naction = random.choice(actions)\ntitle = random.choice(hook_phrases).format(character=character, action=action)\n# Build the prompt for AI node\nPrompt = f\"\"\"\nVideo Analysis Result:\n{_input.first().json.chatInput}\nBased on this, generate a structured JSON output for Google Sheets with the following fields:\n- \"Date\" (MM/DD/YYYY)\n- \"Time\" (HH:MM)\n- \"YouTubeTitle\" (catchy, FOMO-style, MUST be under 90 characters)\n- \"YouTubeTitle2\" (DIFFERENT catchy title, under 90 characters, use a different hook/angle than YouTubeTitle)\n- \"YouTubeDescription\" (engaging, includes CTA like 'watch till the end' or 'subscribe for more')\n- \"YouTubeDescription2\" (DIFFERENT description with different CTA and angle than YouTubeDescription)\n- \"TikTokDescription\" (short, punchy, instant hook)\n- \"FacebookReelDescription\" (attention-grabbing, shareable, engaging)\n- \"InstagramDescription\" (short, emoji-rich, interaction-focused)\n- \"AdditionalNotes\" (hashtags, trends, posting tips)\nSTRICT RULES:\n1. Both \"YouTubeTitle\" and \"YouTubeTitle2\" MUST NOT exceed 90 characters.\n2. YouTubeTitle and YouTubeTitle2 MUST be COMPLETELY DIFFERENT - use different hooks, emotions, or angles.\n3. YouTubeDescription and YouTubeDescription2 MUST be COMPLETELY DIFFERENT - vary the CTAs and storytelling.\n4. The \"Date\" and \"Time\" should be accurate based on the current date and time provided below:\n   - CurrentDate: {date_str}\n   - CurrentTime: {time_str}\n5. The output MUST be valid JSON, properly escaped.\nExample structure:\n{{\n  \"Date\": \"{date_str}\",\n  \"Time\": \"{time_str}\",\n  \"YouTubeTitle\": \"{title}\",\n  \"YouTubeTitle2\": \"...\",\n  \"YouTubeDescription\": \"...\",\n  \"YouTubeDescription2\": \"...\",\n  \"TikTokDescription\": \"...\",\n  \"FacebookReelDescription\": \"...\",\n  \"InstagramDescription\": \"...\",\n  \"AdditionalNotes\": \"...\"\n}}\nCRITICAL: YouTubeTitle and YouTubeTitle2 must be DISTINCT. YouTubeDescription and YouTubeDescription2 must be DISTINCT. Do NOT repeat the same content.\nGenerate irresistible, high-CTR titles and descriptions that make viewers feel they CAN'T miss the video.\n\"\"\"\nreturn {\n    \"chatInput\": Prompt\n}"
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        -1712,
        1424
      ],
